                <h2>Understanding Total Energy Production</h2>
                <p>
                    The Total Energy page provides a comprehensive view of energy production across different countries, showcasing the combined contributions of renewable and non-renewable sources towards meeting national energy needs.
                </p>
                <h4>Key Information:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Renewable Energy Production:</strong> Represents electricity generated from sustainable sources such as solar, wind, hydro, biomass, and geothermal energy.</li>
                    <li><strong>Non-Renewable Energy Production:</strong> Refers to electricity generated from finite resources like coal, oil, natural gas, and nuclear energy.</li>
                    <li><strong>Total Energy Production:</strong> Combines both renewable and non-renewable energy outputs to represent a country's overall energy generation capacity.</li>
                </ul>
                <h4>Implications and Significance:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Understanding the breakdown of energy production helps assess environmental impact and supports sustainability efforts.</li>
                    <li>Total energy production reflects energy security and resilience, reducing dependency on external energy sources.</li>
                    <li>Insights into energy production inform policy decisions and drive innovation towards cleaner energy systems.</li>
                </ul>
                <h4>Why It Matters:</h4>
